    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Mosiah",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 26,
        "summary": "Many members of the Church are led into sin by unbelievers\u2014Alma is promised eternal life\u2014Those who repent and are baptized gain forgiveness\u2014Church members in sin who repent and confess to Alma and to the Lord will be forgiven; otherwise, they will not be numbered among the people of the Church. About 120\u2013100\u00a0B.C.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Now it came to pass that there were many of the rising generation that could not understand the words of king Benjamin, being little children at the time he spake unto his people; and they did not believe the tradition of their fathers.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 2:1.",
                        "start": 96,
                        "end": 101
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Family, Children, Duties of.",
                        "start": 193,
                        "end": 204
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "They did not believe what had been said concerning the resurrection of the dead, neither did they believe concerning the coming of Christ.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And now because of their unbelief they could not understand the word of God; and their hearts were hardened.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Unbelief.",
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 33
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Understanding.",
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 59
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And they would not be baptized; neither would they join the church. And they were a separate people as to their faith, and remained so ever after, even in their carnal and sinful state; for they would not call upon the Lord their God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 25:22 (18\u201323); Alma 4:5 (4\u20135).",
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 66
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Man, Natural, Not Spiritually Reborn.",
                        "start": 161,
                        "end": 167
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And now in the reign of Mosiah they were not half so numerous as the people of God; but because of the dissensions among the brethren they became more numerous.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Apostasy of Individuals.",
                        "start": 103,
                        "end": 114
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For it came to pass that they did deceive many with their flattering words, who were in the church, and did cause them to commit many sins; therefore it became expedient that those who committed sin, that were in the church, should be admonished by the church.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Col. 2:18 (16\u201323). TG\u00a0Deceit.",
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 41
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Flatter.",
                        "start": 58,
                        "end": 68
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 5:57 (57\u201358); 6:3. TG\u00a0Warn.",
                        "start": 235,
                        "end": 245
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 197
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And it came to pass that they were brought before the priests, and delivered up unto the priests by the teachers; and the priests brought them before Alma, who was the high priest.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Priest, Melchizedek Priesthood.",
                        "start": 89,
                        "end": 96
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 23:16; 29:42.",
                        "start": 168,
                        "end": 179
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Now king Mosiah had given Alma the authority over the church.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Delegation of Responsibility.",
                        "start": 35,
                        "end": 44
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Church Organization.",
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 60
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And it came to pass that Alma did not know concerning them; but there were many witnesses against them; yea, the people stood and testified of their iniquity in abundance.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Witness.",
                        "start": 80,
                        "end": 89
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Now there had not any such thing happened before in the church; therefore Alma was troubled in his spirit, and he caused that they should be brought before the king.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And he said unto the king: Behold, here are many whom we have brought before thee, who are accused of their brethren; yea, and they have been taken in divers iniquities. And they do not repent of their iniquities; therefore we have brought them before thee, that thou mayest judge them according to their crimes.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But king Mosiah said unto Alma: Behold, I judge them not; therefore I deliver them into thy hands to be judged.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 42:87 (78\u201393).",
                        "start": 70,
                        "end": 77
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And now the spirit of Alma was again troubled; and he went and inquired of the Lord what he should do concerning this matter, for he feared that he should do wrong in the sight of God.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And it came to pass that after he had poured out his whole soul to God, the voice of the Lord came to him, saying:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Guidance, Divine.",
                        "start": 76,
                        "end": 81
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Blessed art thou, Alma, and blessed are they who were baptized in the waters of Mormon. Thou art blessed because of thy exceeding faith in the words alone of my servant Abinadi.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 18:30.",
                        "start": 70,
                        "end": 86
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 17:2; D&C 46:14. TG\u00a0Faith.",
                        "start": 130,
                        "end": 135
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And blessed are they because of their exceeding faith in the words alone which thou hast spoken unto them.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And blessed art thou because thou hast established a church among this people; and they shall be established, and they shall be my people.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 25:19 (19\u201324).",
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 59
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Yea, blessed is this people who are willing to bear my name; for in my name shall they be called; and they are mine.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 1:11; 5:8. TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Taking the Name of.",
                        "start": 55,
                        "end": 59
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 28:10.",
                        "start": 71,
                        "end": 75
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And because thou hast inquired of me concerning the transgressor, thou art blessed.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Thou art my servant; and I covenant with thee that thou shalt have eternal life; and thou shalt serve me and go forth in my name, and shalt gather together my sheep.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Election.",
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 79
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And he that will hear my voice shall be my sheep; and him shall ye receive into the church, and him will I also receive.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Good Shepherd.",
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 48
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For behold, this is my church; whosoever is baptized shall be baptized unto repentance. And whomsoever ye receive shall believe in my name; and him will I freely forgive.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 27:13.",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Head of the Church.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 29
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 9:23.",
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 52
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Baptism, Qualifications for.",
                        "start": 120,
                        "end": 127
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Remission of Sins.",
                        "start": 162,
                        "end": 169
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For it is I that taketh upon me the sins of the world; for it is I that hath created them; and it is I that granteth unto him that believeth unto the end a place at my right hand.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Redeemer.",
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 40
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Creator.",
                        "start": 77,
                        "end": 84
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 198
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For behold, in my name are they called; and if they know me they shall come forth, and shall have a place eternally at my right hand.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 17:3.",
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 56
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And it shall come to pass that when the second trump shall sound then shall they that never knew me come forth and shall stand before me.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Dan. 12:2 (1\u20132).",
                        "start": 40,
                        "end": 46
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "3\u00a0Ne. 14:23 (21\u201323); D&C 76:85 (81\u201386); 112:26.",
                        "start": 92,
                        "end": 96
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And then shall they know that I am the Lord their God, that I am their Redeemer; but they would not be redeemed.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And then I will confess unto them that I never knew them; and they shall depart into everlasting fire prepared for the devil and his angels.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 7:23 (21\u201323).",
                        "start": 47,
                        "end": 51
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 13:27.",
                        "start": 73,
                        "end": 79
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 15:35 (32\u201336).",
                        "start": 85,
                        "end": 96
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore I say unto you, that he that will not hear my voice, the same shall ye not receive into my church, for him I will not receive at the last day.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 9:31; D&C 1:14 (2, 11, 14); Moses 6:27.",
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 52
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore I say unto you, Go; and whosoever transgresseth against me, him shall ye judge according to the sins which he has committed; and if he confess his sins before thee and me, and repenteth in the sincerity of his heart, him shall ye forgive, and I will forgive him also.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Judgment.",
                        "start": 83,
                        "end": 88
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Accountability.",
                        "start": 89,
                        "end": 98
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Num. 5:7 (6\u201310); Alma 17:4; 3\u00a0Ne. 1:25. TG\u00a0Confession.",
                        "start": 145,
                        "end": 152
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Repent.",
                        "start": 186,
                        "end": 195
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Forgive.",
                        "start": 240,
                        "end": 247
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Yea, and as often as my people repent will I forgive them their trespasses against me.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moro. 6:8.",
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 11
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ezek. 33:11 (11, 15\u201316); Amos 5:4 (4\u20138); Acts 3:19 (19\u201320); 2\u00a0Ne. 1:20; Mosiah 29:20.",
                        "start": 31,
                        "end": 37
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And ye shall also forgive one another your trespasses; for verily I say unto you, he that forgiveth not his neighbor's trespasses when he says that he repents, the same hath brought himself under condemnation.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Col. 3:13 (12\u201314); 3\u00a0Ne. 13:14 (14\u201315); D&C 64:10 (9\u201310).",
                        "start": 18,
                        "end": 25
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Neighbor.",
                        "start": 108,
                        "end": 118
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Now I say unto you, Go; and whosoever will not repent of his sins the same shall not be numbered among my people; and this shall be observed from this time forward.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 1:24. TG\u00a0Excommunication.",
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 53
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And it came to pass when Alma had heard these words he wrote them down that he might have them, and that he might judge the people of that church according to the commandments of God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Scriptures, Writing of.",
                        "start": 55,
                        "end": 60
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And it came to pass that Alma went and judged those that had been taken in iniquity, according to the word of the Lord.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 33:14 (13\u201315).",
                        "start": 102,
                        "end": 106
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And whosoever repented of their sins and did confess them, them he did number among the people of the church;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Confession.",
                        "start": 45,
                        "end": 52
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And those that would not confess their sins and repent of their iniquity, the same were not numbered among the people of the church, and their names were blotted out.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 32:33; Ps. 9:5; 109:13; Alma 1:24. TG\u00a0Book of Life.",
                        "start": 154,
                        "end": 165
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And it came to pass that Alma did regulate all the affairs of the church; and they began again to have peace and to prosper exceedingly in the affairs of the church, walking circumspectly before God, receiving many, and baptizing many.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And now all these things did Alma and his fellow laborers do who were over the church, walking in all diligence, teaching the word of God in all things, suffering all manner of afflictions, being persecuted by all those who did not belong to the church of God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Church Organization.",
                        "start": 42,
                        "end": 57
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Walking with God.",
                        "start": 87,
                        "end": 94
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And they did admonish their brethren; and they were also admonished, every one by the word of God, according to his sins, or to the sins which he had committed, being commanded of God to pray without ceasing, and to give thanks in all things.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Warn.",
                        "start": 57,
                        "end": 67
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 32:9 (8\u20139).",
                        "start": 187,
                        "end": 191
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Thanksgiving.",
                        "start": 221,
                        "end": 227
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 199
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}